(44, 'The differential coefficient of f[logx] when  f(x) = logx is ', 'xlogx', '$ \\frac{x}{logx} $', '$ \\frac{logx}{x} $', '$ \\frac{1}{xlogx} $', ' f(x)=logx $\\Rightarrow$ f(logx) = log(logx)</br>\r\n       so,$\\dfrac{df(logx)}{dx}= \\dfrac{1}{logx} .\\dfrac{1}{x} = \\dfrac{1}{xlogx}$ \r\n', '0', 'C'),
(45, 'If $ \\sin^2\\theta=\\frac{1}{4},$ the most general value of $\\theta$ is', '$ 2n\\pi\\pm(-1)^n\\frac{\\pi}{6} $', ' $ 2n\\pi\\pm\\frac{\\pi}{6} $', '$ \\frac{n\\pi}{2}\\pm(-1)^n\\frac{\\pi}{6} $', '$ n\\pi\\pm\\frac{\\pi}{6} $', ' $\\sin^2\\theta=\\dfrac{1}{4} \\Rightarrow \\sin^2\\theta=\\sin^2(\\pi/6) \\Rightarrow \\theta = n\\pi \\pm \\dfrac{\\pi}{6} $', '0', 'C'),
(46, 'The function f: R $\\longrightarrow $ R defined by $ f(x) =x^2 + x $ is = ', 'one-one into', 'one-one onto', 'many- one onto', 'many one into', ' Quadratic equations are many to one and into.', '0', 'C'),
