(48, 'The incomplete quadratic equation is', '$ ax^2 + c =0, c\\neq 0 $', '$ ax^2 bx + c =0, a\\neq 0 , b\\neq 0 $', '$ ax^2 + c =0, a\\neq 0 $', '$ ax^2 bx + c =0, a = 0 $', 'A function f is defined by f(x)=$ a_0x^n + a_1x^{n-1} + ...............+ a_{n-1}x + a_n (a_0\\neq 0) $', '0', 'C'),
(49, '$ \\lim_{x \\to \\infty}\\left(1+\\frac{3}{n}\\right)^{3n} = $', '$ e^3 $', '$ e^6 $', '$ e$', '$ e^9 $', ' $ \\lim_{x \\to \\infty}\\left(1+\\frac{3}{n}\\right)^{3n} = (e^3)^3 = e^9 $ </br>\r\n    since $ \\lim_{x \\to \\infty}\\left(1+\\frac{x}{n}\\right)^{n} = e^n $ ', '0', 'C'),
(50, '$ \\int a^{log_a(2^x)}dx= $', '$ 2^x +c $', '2', '$ xlog_a 2$', '$2^xlog_2e$', ' Let y = $ a^{log_a(2)^x} \\Rightarrow logy= loga^{log_a(2)^x} $</br>\r\n     $\\Rightarrow logy=log_a2^xloga.$ </br>\r\n    logy = $\\dfrac{log2^x}{loga} loga = log2^x $</br>\r\n    so, $ y= 2^x $ </br>\r\n    I = $\\int2^x = \\dfrac{2^x}{log_e2} + c $ </br>\r\n     =$\\dfrac{2^x}{\\dfrac{1}{log_2e}} + c= 2^xlog_2e + C$ ', '0', 'C'),
(51, ' If $ A= \\begin {pmatrix} 				K & 2 \\\\ 			        2 & K 				\\end {pmatrix} $ and $ |A^3|= 125 $ then the value of K is', '$\\pm1$', '$\\pm2$', '$\\pm5$', '$\\pm3$', ' $\\Rightarrow |A^3|= 125,\\Rightarrow A= 5$ </br>\r\n       $\\Rightarrow A=K^2 - 4 $ (from  matrix) </br>\r\n       $\\Rightarrow 5 = K^2 - 4 \\Rightarrow k^2 = 9 $</br>\r\n       $\\Rightarrow = \\pm 3$', '0', 'D'),
(52, 'The area of trianle formed by the lines x =0, y = 0, and $ \\frac{x}{a} + \\frac{y}{b} = 1 $ is ', 'ab sq.units', '2ab  sq.units', '3ab sq.units', '$ \\frac{ab}{2} $ sq.units', ' Area= $\\dfrac{1}{2}\\begin {bmatrix}\r\n				0 & 0 & 1 \\\\\r\n			        a & 0 & 1 \\\\\r\n                                0 & b & 1\r\n				\\end {bmatrix} $ </br>\r\n\r\n      =$\\dfrac{1}{2}$(ab-0) </br>\r\n      =$\\dfrac{ab}{2} $', '0', 'D'),
