(54, ' if $ y= 1 + x + \\frac{x^2}{2!} + \\frac{x^3}{3!} + ...............then \\frac{dy}{dx} = $ ', '1 - y', 'y + 1', '- y', 'y', ' $ y= 1 + x + \\frac{x^2}{2!} + \\frac{x^3}{3!} + ..............= e^x $ </br>\r\n       $ \\dfrac{dy}{dx}=e^x = y $', '0', 'D'),
(55, 'If $ \\tan\\theta=\\cot\\alpha,$ then the genera; solution is', '$ \\theta=n\\pi -\\frac{\\pi}{2} +\\alpha $', '$ \\theta=n\\pi +\\frac{\\pi}{2} +\\alpha $', '$ \\theta=n\\pi -\\frac{\\pi}{2} -\\alpha $', ' $ \\theta=n\\pi +\\frac{\\pi}{2} -\\alpha $', ' $ \\tan\\theta=\\cot\\alpha $</br>\r\n    $\\Rightarrow\\tan\\theta=\\tan\\left(\\dfrac{\\pi}{2}- \\alpha\\right) \\Rightarrow \\theta=n\\pi +\\frac{\\pi}{2} -\\alpha $ \r\n', '0', 'D'),
(56, 'The domain of f(x) = $ \\sqrt{4x-x^2} $', 'R - [0, 4]', 'R - (0, 4)', '(0, 4)', '[0, 4]', ' Other than [0, 4] gives under root -ve sign.', '0', 'D'),
(57, 'perpendicular distance of the point  (3, 4, 5) from y-axis is ', '$\\sqrt{41} $', '4', '5', '$\\sqrt{34} $', ' If P (a, b, c) be any point.</br>\r\n    Shortest distance at P from y-axis is $\\sqrt{a^2 + c^2} $unit.</br>\r\n    So,perpendicular distance=$\\sqrt{9+25}=\\sqrt{34}$ units.', '0', 'D'),
(58, '$ \\int a^x da = $', '$ \\frac{a^x}{log_ea}+ c $', '$ a^x + c$', '$log_ea$', 'none', '  $\\int a^xdx=a^xlog_ae= \\frac{a^x}{log_e^a}$', '0', 'D'),
(59, ' $ \\lim_{x \\to 0} \\frac{sinx^g}{x} $', '$\\frac{\\pi}{100}$', '$200\\pi$', '$100\\pi$', '$\\frac{\\pi}{200}$', '  $ \\lim_{x \\to 0} \\dfrac{sinx^g}{x} $ </br>\r\n      $\\Rightarrow \\lim_{x \\to 0} \\dfrac{sinx^g}{\\dfrac{200x}{\\pi}}=\\dfrac{\\pi}{200}\\lim_{x \\to 0} \\dfrac{sinx^g}{x^g} $ </br>\r\n      =$\\dfrac{\\pi}{200}$', '0', 'D'),
(60, 'Both the roots of the equation $ x^2 +bx+c=0$ and $x^2 +dx + e =0$ &  are equal then', 'bc = dc', 'bd = ce', '$ b^2d = c^2e $', 'be = cd', '  If roots are equql coefficient are proportional,</br>\r\n     $\\dfrac{b}{d}=\\dfrac{c}{e} \\Rightarrow be=cd$', '0', 'D'),
(61, 'If A and B are two sets such that $ A\\cap B\\neq\\phi $ then A - (A - B) is equal to', 'A', 'B', ' B - 2A', '$ A\\cap B$', ' A - (A - B) = A - A only = A$\\cap$B', '0', 'E'),
(62, 'If f(0) = 1, f(1) = 2,  f(2) = 5 ,f(3) = 10, then f(-1) is', '0', '1', '11', '2', ' From the given, we can find f(x)=$x^2$ + 1 </br>\r\n       f(-1)= (-1)<sup>2</sup> + 1 = 2 ', '0', 'E'),
(63, '$ \\lim_{x \\to  3}$ is equal to', '0', '1', '-1', 'doesn''t  exist', '$ \\lim_{x \\to 3}\\dfrac{x - 3}{|x -3|}$= +ve,$ \\lim_{x \\to 3^-}\\dfrac{x - 3}{|x -3|}$= -ve</br>\r\n\r\n       LHL$\\neq$RHL so.limit doesn''t exit.', '0', 'E'),
(64, 'The value of $ \\lambda $ , for which the equation $ 4x^2 + 20x + \\lambda=0 $ has its one roots equal to zero, is ', '-1', '1', '-5', '0', ' since the eqn has one root equal to 0,itmust satisfy 0.</br>\r\n     4(0)<sup>2</sup> + 20(0) + $\\lambda$ = 0 $\\Rightarrow \\lambda=0$ ', '0', 'E'),
(65, 'The principle value of $\\theta $ which satisfied $ sin\\theta=\\frac{\\sqrt{3} }{2}$ and $ cos\\theta =\\frac{1}{2}$ is ', '$ \\frac{\\pi}{4} $', '$ \\frac{\\pi}{2} $', '$ \\frac{\\pi}{6} $', '$ \\frac{\\pi}{3} $', ' $\\sin\\theta=\\dfrac{\\sqrt{3}}{2},\\theta$ = sin<sup>-1</sup>$\\dfrac{\\sqrt{3}}{2}  = \\dfrac{\\pi}{3}$', '0', 'E'),
(66, 'If $ A= \\begin {pmatrix} 				0 & 3 \\\\ 			        k-5 & 0 				\\end {pmatrix} $ is skew symmetric matrix then k equals ', '0', '5', '8', '2', ' k - 5 = -3 $\\Rightarrow$ k = 2', '0', 'E'),
(67, 'If the coordinate of P and Q are (2, 3, 4) and (1, -2, 1) respectively,then the lines OP and OQ are ', 'inclined at $ 45^ {\\circ} $', 'parallel', 'coincident', 'perpendicular', ' Let O be the origin,the d.r''s of line OP is 2, 3, 4. and that of OQ is 1, -2, 1</br>\r\n       $\\Rightarrow 1\\times 2+(-2)\\times 3 + 4\\times 1 = 0$ ', '0', 'E'),
(68, 'The direction cosine of a line joining the points M(2, 3, 5) and (-1, 3, 2) are', '$ \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}},\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}},\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}} $', '$ -\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}},0,\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}} $', ' $ 0,\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}},0 $', ' $ \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}},0,\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}} $', ' Direction cosine of the line = l, m, n </br>\r\n       =$\\cos\\alpha,\\cos\\beta,\\cos\\delta=\\dfrac{x_2-x_1}{r}, \\dfrac{y_2-y_1}{r}, \\dfrac{z_2-z_1}{r} $</br>\r\n        $\\dfrac{2+1}{\\sqrt{3^2+0^2+3^2}}, \\dfrac{3-3}{\\sqrt{3^2+0^2+3^2}}, \\dfrac{5-2}{\\sqrt{3^2+0^2+3^2}}$</br>\r\n       $\\dfrac{1}{\\sqrt{2}}, 0, \\dfrac{1}{\\sqrt{2}} $', '0', 'E'),
(69, 'The distance between the parallel planes 2x - 2y + z - 6 = 0 and 4x - 4y + 2z - 7 =0 is ', '5', '$ \\frac{5}{\\sqrt{6}}$', '6', '$ \\frac{5}{6}$', ' find any point on the eqn </br>\r\n     Let x= 0 and y= 0 in 2x - 2y +z - 6 = 0</br>\r\n     $\\Rightarrow $ z= 0 </br>\r\n  Now, perpendicular distance from (0,0,6) on 4x - 4y + 2z -7 = 0 is required  ans</br>\r\n  d=$\\dfrac{4\\times0-4\\times0 +2(6)}{\\sqrt{16 +16+4}}=\\dfrac{5}{6}$ ', '0', 'E'),
(70, 'The equation formed by decreasing each root of $ ax^2 + bx + c = 0$ by 1 is $ 2x^2 + 8x + 2 = 0 $ then', 'a = -b', 'c = -a', 'b = a + c', 'b = - c', ' ax<sup>2</sup>+bx+c=0, replace x by x+1;</br>\r\n        a(x+1)<sup>2</sup>+b(x+1)+c=0</br>\r\n    $\\Rightarrow$  ax<sup>2</sup>+x(2a+b)+(a+b+c)=0</br>\r\n    comparing with  2x<sup>2</sup>+8x+2 </br>\r\n    a=2, 2a+b=8</br>\r\n    b=4 and a+b+c= 2</br>\r\n   c=-4 so, b=-c', '0', 'E');
