(9, 'The n<sup>th</sup> term of the series is (2n-1) the sum of 1<sup>st</sup> n terms is :', 'n (n+1)', 'n<sup>2</sup>-n', '$ \\dfrac{n(n+1)}{2} $', 'n<sup>2</sup>', 'd', 'Put n=2 then </br>\r\n <br> t<sub>1</sub>= 2*1 -1 =1 </br>\r\n  <br> t<sub>2</sub>= 2*2 -1 =3 </br>\r\n  <br> Sum of 1<sup>th</sup> 2 terms = 4 </br>\r\n  <br> Put n=2 in options then option a=6, option b=2, option c=3 and option d=4. </br>\r\n  <br> Hence, correct answer is option d.', 0),
(10, 'Given that a<sup>x</sup>=b<sup>y</sup>=c<sup>z</sup>=d<sup>v</sup> and a,b,c,d are in G.P. then x,y,z,v are in:', 'A.P.', 'G.P.', 'H.P.', 'None', 'c', 'Let a,b,c,d=2,4,8,16 be in G.P. Then, 2<sup>x</sup>=2<sup>2y</sup>=2<sup>3z</sup>=2<sup>4v</sup> </br>\r\n	<br> To satisfy this equation, answer should be in x,y,z,V =1,$ \\dfrac{1}{2}, \\dfrac{1}{3},  \\dfrac{1}{4} $ </br>\r\n	<br> Note:When you put x=1, 2<sup>x</sup>=2, according to equation 2<sup>2y</sup>=2 so, y= $ \\dfrac{1}{2} $ </br>\r\n	<br> Hence, correct option is option c.', 0),
(11, 'If H is the Harmonic mean between a and b, then $ \\dfrac{1}{H-a} + \\dfrac{1}{H-b} $ equals to :', 'a+b', '$ \\dfrac{1}{a} - \\dfrac{1}{b} $', 'a-b', '$ \\dfrac{1}{a} + \\dfrac{1}{b} $', 'd', 'Let a,H,b =1cm, 0.5cm and $ \\dfrac{1}{3} $ cm . Then, </br>\r\n	<br> $ \\dfrac{1}{H-a} + \\dfrac{1}{H-b}  =  \\dfrac{1}{ \\dfrac{1}{2} -1} + \\dfrac{1}{ \\dfrac{1}{2}- \\dfrac{1}{3}} $ = -2 +6 =4 </br>\r\n	<br> Here, option a and c cannot be right answers. Why? dimensionally they are incorrect. answer must be cm<sup>-1</sup> form. </br>\r\n	<br>So,  check only option b and d. </br>\r\n	<br> b) 1-3 = -2    and d) 1+3=4 </br>\r\n	<br> Hence, option d is correct.', 0),
(12, 'Sum of 2+22+222+2222+ ............ to n terms is', '$ \\dfrac{2}{9} \\left [ \\dfrac{10(10^n -1 )}{9} - n \\right ] $', '2n', '2<sup>n</sup>', '$ \\dfrac{9}{2} \\left [ \\dfrac{10(10^n -1 )}{2} - n \\right ] $', 'a', 'Put n=2, but better to use n=higher values for accuracy.Let check with n=2. </br>\r\n	<br> if n=2 then ,2+22=24 </br>\r\n	<br> option a=24, option b=4, option c=4 and option d=2218.5  [substituing n=2 in options] </br>\r\n	<br>We encounter two option b and c =4.Suppose question had value 4. In such case change value of n (let n=3 but check only in the options which gave same value previously.Other two options can be declared to be wrong fromn previous substitution only. </br>\r\n	<br> Anyways, in this case correct option is a.', 0),
(13, 'If a,b,c are in A.P., b,c,d are in G.P. and c,d,e are in H.P., then a,c,e are 	in', 'A.P.', 'G.P.', 'H.P.', 'None', 'b', 'Let a,b,c = 2,4,6(they are in A.P). Then, accordingly </br>\r\n	<br> For b,c,d to be in G.P. d=9.  How? c= $ \\sqrt{bd} = \\sqrt{4 \\times d} $ i.e. $ b^2 $ = 4d which gives d= 36/4=9. Similarly, </br>\r\n	<br> For c,d,e to be in H.P e=18. </br>\r\n		<br> We get a,c,e=2,6,18 which is in G.P. </br>\r\n		<br> Hence, correct option is b.', 0),
(14, 'If a,b,c,d,e are in G.P., then e/c=', 'd/b', 'a/c', 'b/e', 'a/e', 'a', 'Let a,b,c,d,e= 2,4,8,16,32 (G.P) . Then e/c=32/8=4 </br>\r\n	<br> a) d/b=4 </br>\r\n	<br> b) a/c=1/4 </br>\r\n	<br> c) b/e=1/8 </br>\r\n	<br> d) a/e = 1/16 </br>\r\n	<br> Therefore, correct answer is a.', 0),
(15, 'If a,b,c are in H.P., then', 'a<sup>2</sup>+b<sup>2</sup>>c<sup>2</sup>', 'a<sup>2</sup>+c<sup>2</sup>>2b<sup>2</sup>', 'a<sup>2</sup>+b<sup>2</sup>>2c<sup>2</sup>', 'none', 'b', 'Take values of a,b and c which are in H.P. Example 1, $ \\dfrac{1}{2} , \\dfrac{1}{3} $ </br>\r\n	<br> Now, checking the values in options, We get option b as correct.', 0),
(16, 'The n<sup>th</sup> term of the series 1+ ( 1+x) + (1 + x +x<sup>2</sup>) + ........ n terms is (x<0)', '$ \\dfrac{1- x^n}{1-x} $', '$ \\dfrac{x(1- x^n)}{1-x} $', '$ \\dfrac{n(1-x)-x(1- x^n)}{1-x} $', '$ \\dfrac{1+ x^n}{1-x} $', 'a', 'Let x=0.5 then , 2<sup>th</sup> term = 1+ 0.5 = 1.5 </br>\r\n	<br> a) $ \\dfrac{1- 0.5^2}{1-0.5} $ = 1.5 </br>\r\n	<br> b) $ \\dfrac{0.5(1- 0.5^2)}{1-0.5} $= 0.75 </br>\r\n	<br> c) $ \\dfrac{2(1-0.5)-0.5(1- 0.5^2)}{1-0.5} $=1.25 </br>\r\n	<br> d) $ \\dfrac{1+ 0.5^2}{1-0.5} $= 2.5 </br>\r\n	<br> Hence, opton a is correct.', 0),
(17, 'The value of sec<sup>-1</sup>(-x) is ?', 'sec<sup>-1</sup>x', '-sec<sup>-1</sup>x', '$ \\pi $ - sec<sup>-1</sup>x', '2 $ \\pi $ - sec<sup>-1</sup>x', 'c', 'In these kind of question, we should substitute the value of x which is in the domain.Put x=2 which is in the domain of sec<sup>-1</sup>x </br>\r\n	<br> So, sec<sup>-1</sup>(-2) =120 </br>\r\n	<br> Check option with same value of x. </br>\r\n	<br> a) 60 		b) -60 	c) 120		d) 300 </br>\r\n	<br> Hence, correct option is c.', 0),
(18, 'If $ \\tan \\left ( \\dfrac{2x}{1-X^2} \\right ) + \\cot \\left ( \\dfrac{1-x^2}{2x} \\right ) = \\pi $, then =', '0.5', '1', '2', '0', 'b', '<br> Set in calculator as $ \\tan \\left ( \\dfrac{2x}{1-x^2} \\right ) +  \\cot \\left ( \\dfrac{1-x^2}{2x} \\right ) - \\pi $ and press calc. </br>\r\n	<br> Put option a and press ans. Check if it equals zero. if it does it is correct answer else not. Repeat this with all options. Only one option wil give result zero which is correct answer. </br>\r\n	<br> Hence, correct option is b.', 0),
(19, 'The value of cosec( 2 tan<sup>-1</sup>x ) =', '$ \\dfrac{1+x^2}{2x} $', '$ \\dfrac{2x}{1-x^2} $', '$ \\dfrac {1 - x^2}{1+x^2} $', '$ \\dfrac{1+x^2}{1-x^2} $', 'a', 'Put any value from the domain of tan<sup>-1</sup>x  and use calculator. </br>\r\n	<br> cosec( 2 tan<sup>-1</sup>x )= cosec(2 * 63.44)= $ \\dfrac{1}{ \\sin { (2 \\times 63.44) } } $ = 1.25 </br>\r\n	<br> Put x=2 in option which gives option a=1.2, b = -1.33  c= $ \\dfrac{-3}{5} $ and d= -1.67. </br>\r\n	<br> Hence, correct option is a.', 0),
(20, 'If cos<sup>-1</sup>x+cos<sup>-1</sup>y+cos<sup>-1</sup>z = $ \\pi $, then', 'x + y + z =xyz', 'xy + yz + zx =1', 'x<sup>2</sup>+y<sup>2</sup>+z<sup>2</sup>+2xyz =1', 'x<sup>2</sup>+y<sup>2</sup>+2xyz =1', 'c', 'Here, cos<sup>-1</sup>x+cos<sup>-1</sup>y+cos<sup>-1</sup>z = 180 </br>\r\n	<br> let x=y=z=0.5 </br>\r\n	<br> 60 + 60 + 60 =180 </br>\r\n	<br> Then, cos<sup>-1</sup>x+cos<sup>-1</sup>y+cos<sup>-1</sup>z = cos<sup>-1</sup>(0.5)+cos<sup>-1</sup>(0.5)+cos<sup>-1</sup>(0.5) </br>\r\n	<br> Let x=y=z=0.5 </br>\r\n	<br> Put these values in option. Better to take differnet values for x, y and z but it may be time consuming. </br>\r\n	<br> a) $ \\dfrac{3}{2} = \\dfrac{1}{8} $ which is false. </br>\r\n	<br> b) $ \\dfrac{3}{4} = 1 $ which is false. </br>\r\n	<br> c) $ \\dfrac{3}{4} + \\dfrac{1}{4}=1 $ , which is true. </br>\r\n	<br> d) $ \\dfrac{1}{2} + \\dfrac{2}{8}=1 $ , which is false. </br>\r\n	<br> Hence, correct option is c.', 0),
(21, 'If x + $ \\dfrac{1}{x} $ =2, then the principle value of sin<sup>-1</sup>x is,', '$ \\dfrac{ \\pi }{6} $', '$ \\dfrac{ \\pi }{2} $', '$ \\dfrac{ \\pi }{4} $', '$ \\dfrac{3 \\pi }{2} $', 'b', 'Given is: x + $ \\dfrac{1}{x} $ =2. </br>\r\n	<br> This condition is satisfied by putting x=1. </br>\r\n	<br> Hence, sin<sup>-1</sup>1= $ \\dfrac{ \\pi }{2} $ </br>\r\n	<br> Therefore, option b is correct answer.', 0),
(22, 'If sec<sup>-1</sup>x = cosec<sup>-1</sup>y , then the value of $ \\dfrac{1}{x^2} + \\dfrac{1}{y^2} $ =', '-1', '1', '0', '$ \\dfrac{1}{2} $', 'b', 'Put y=2(assume), then form condition ,sec<sup>-1</sup>x = cosec<sup>-1</sup>2 </br> $ \\Rightarrow $ x= sec(30)= $ \\dfrac{2}{ \\sqrt{3} } $. Hence, </br>\r\n		<br> Put value of x and y in question. </br>\r\n		<br> $ \\dfrac{1}{ { \\dfrac{2}{ \\sqrt {3} } }^2 } + \\dfrac{1}{{ (2) }^2 } = 1 $ </br>\r\n		<br> Hence, correct answer is option b.', 0),
(23, 'The value of sin cot<sup>-1</sup>cos tan <sup>-1</sup> x equals :', '$ \\sqrt { \\dfrac{1+x^2}{2+x^2} } $', '$ \\sqrt { \\dfrac{2+x^2}{1+x^2} } $', '$ \\sqrt { \\dfrac{1-x^2}{1+x^2} } $', '$  \\dfrac{2x}{ \\sqrt {1+x^2} }  $', 'a', 'Put x=1, </br>\r\n	<br> sin cot<sup>-1</sup>cos tan <sup>-1</sup> 1 = sin cot<sup>-1</sup>cos 45 = sin cot<sup>-1</sup> $ \\left ( \\dfrac{1}{ \\sqrt{2} } \\right ) $ </br>\r\n		<br> =sin tan <sup>-1</sup> ( $ \\sqrt{2} $ ) = 0.082 </br>\r\n		<br> Note: You can directly use a calculator , i.e. at first type tan<sup>-1</sup>1 in calculator, then press ''=''. </br>\r\n		<br> After that type " cos Ans" . Now you may get confused how to type cot<sup>-1</sup> in calculator; so for this type <br>\r\n		<br> "tan<sup>-1</sup> $ \\left ( \\dfrac{1}{ans} \\right ) $ ". Finally type "sin ans". Your ans is ready in calculator.  </br>\r\n		<br> Now check optionwith x=1. </br>\r\n		<br> a) $ \\sqrt { \\dfrac{2}{3} } $  = 0.82 </br>\r\n		<br> b) $ \\sqrt { \\dfrac{3}{2} } $  = 1.225 </br>\r\n		<br> c)  $ \\sqrt { \\dfrac{0}{2} } $  = 0 </br>\r\n		<br> d) ${ \\dfrac{2}{ \\sqrt{2}} } $  = 1.414 </br>\r\n		<br> Hence, correct option is a.', 0),
(24, 'The general values of $ \\theta $ inthe equation tan 5 $ \\theta $ = cot5 $ \\theta $ :', '(2n+1) $ \\dfrac{ \\pi }{2} $', '2n$ \\pi $', 'n $ \\pi $ + $ \\dfrac{ \\pi }{4} $', '(2n+1) $ \\dfrac{ \\pi }{14} $', 'd', 'tan5 $ \\theta $ = cot2 $ \\theta $ = tan $ \\left ( \\dfrac{ \\pi } {2} - 2 \\theta \\right ) \\Rightarrow 5 \\theta $ = n $ \\pi $ + $ \\left ( \\dfrac{ \\pi } {2} - 2 \\theta \\right ) $ </br>\r\n		<br> $ \\therefore \\theta $ = (2n+1) $ \\dfrac{ \\pi }{14} $  </br>\r\n		\r\n		<br> In the given options put n= any integer ( 1, 2, ...). Then substitute the result in the question. </br>\r\n		<br>Which satisfies the given equation , is the required option . For eg: take n=1. </br>\r\n		<br> option a= (2n+1) $ \\dfrac{ \\pi }{2} $ = $ \\dfrac { \\pi }{2} $ </br>\r\n		<br> option b= 2n$ \\pi $= 2 $ \\pi $ </br>\r\n		<br> option c= n $ \\pi $ + $ \\dfrac{ \\pi }{4} $ = $ \\dfrac{5 \\pi }{4} $ </br>\r\n		<br> option d= (2n+1) $ \\dfrac{ \\pi }{14} $ = $ \\dfrac{3 \\pi }{14} $ </br>\r\n		<br> Put these values in question. Only option d satisfies the equation. So, it is required answer.', 0),
(25, 'The equation $ \\sqrt{3} $sinx- cosx = $ \\sqrt{2} $ has general solution in x equals :', 'n$ \\pi \\pm \\dfrac{ \\pi }{6} $', 'n$ \\pi \\pm { (-1) }^n \\dfrac{ \\pi }{4} + \\dfrac{ \\pi } {6} $', '2n$ \\pi \\pm \\dfrac{ \\pi }{4} $', 'n$ \\pi \\pm \\dfrac{ \\pi }{3} $', 'b', 'Subtitute any value of x such that all option are different. In this case n=0 works but n=3 or 5 will be better. </br>\r\n		<br> a) $ \\dfrac{ \\pi }{ 6 } = 30^\\circ $  </br>\r\n		<br> b) $  \\dfrac{ \\pi }{ 4 } +  \\dfrac{ \\pi }{ 6 } = 75^\\circ $ </br>\r\n		<br> c) $ \\dfrac{ \\pi }{ 4 } = 45^\\circ $ </br>\r\n		<br> d) $ \\dfrac{ \\pi }{ 3 } = 60^\\circ $ </br>\r\n		<br> Put these values in question. For simplicity type, $ \\sqrt{3} $sinx- cosx - $ \\sqrt{2} $ in calculator and press calc. </br>\r\n		<br> Provide above options and check. If answer equals 0, then it satisfies above eqation and it is correct option. </br>\r\n		<br> In this case, option b is correct option.', 0),
(26, 'The general solution of $ 5 { \\cos }^2x + 2 \\cos \\left ( \\dfrac{x}{2} \\right ) +1 =0 $ is', '$ \\dfrac{n \\pi }{4} $', '$ n \\pi  + {(-1)}^n \\dfrac{ \\pi }{6} $', '$ \\dfrac{ n \\pi } {2} + \\dfrac{ \\pi }{3} $', '2n $ \\pi $', 'd', 'Put n=3, then option becomes </br>\r\n		<br> a=135  b=510 c=330 d=1140(taking + sign) </br>\r\n		<br> Now type, $ 5 { \\cos }^2x + 2 \\cos \\left ( \\dfrac{x}{2} \\right ) +1 $ in calculator and press calc button. Check  for all option a,b,c,d. </br>\r\n		 <br> We get required answer answer 0 from option d. Hence , it is correct option.', 0),
(27, 'If $ { \\cos } ^2 \\theta = \\dfrac{1}{4} $ then the general value of $ \\theta $ is,', 'n$ \\pi + \\dfrac{ \\pi }{3} $', 'n$ \\pi \\pm \\dfrac{ \\pi }{3} $', '2n$ \\pi \\pm \\dfrac{ \\pi }{3} $', 'n$ \\pi + { (-1) }^n \\dfrac{ \\pi }{3} $', 'b', 'Question is in square form. So anwer must be in $ \\pm $ form. So, option a and d cannot be right answers. </br>\r\n		 <br> Now, take n=3, then options become </br>\r\n		 <br> b)240( taking +) </br>\r\n		 <br> b) 120(taking -) </br>\r\n		 <br> c) 1140 (taking +) </br>\r\n		 <br> d) 1020 ( taking -) </br>\r\n		 <br> Here, equation is satisfied by both option. change value of n=( other prime number). The one which satisfies question will be the answer. </br>\r\n		 <br> If the solution is satisfied again then take the smaller answer in among the solution. In this case option b will be required answer.', 0),
(28, 'The general solution of sinx+sin2x+sin3x = cosx+cos2x+cos3x is', '$ n \\pi \\pm \\dfrac{ \\pi } {6} $', '$ 2n \\pi \\pm \\dfrac{2 \\pi }{3}  $', '$ \\dfrac{n \\pi }{2} + \\dfrac{ \\pi }{3} $', '(2n+1)$ \\dfrac{ \\pi }{2} $', 'b', 'Here, putting n=0, all terms are different i.e. $  \\dfrac{ \\pi}{6},  \\dfrac{ 2\\pi}{3},  \\dfrac{ \\pi}{3},  \\dfrac{ \\pi}{2} $. </br>\r\n		<br>Type in calculator sinx+sin2x+sin3x - cosx+cos2x+cos3x and press calc. </br>\r\n		<br> Enter 30 and ans. Similarly , put 120 ,60 and 90. The answer will be 0 by option b only.', 0),
(29, 'The value of the determinant $ \\begin{bmatrix}\r\n						1 & bc& a(b+c) \\\\\r\n						1 & ca& b(c+a) \\\\\r\n						1 & ab& c(a+b)\r\n						\\end{bmatrix} $ =', '0', '1', 'abc', 'ab+ bc+ ca', 'a', 'In case of such matrix problem, solution can easily be found by keeping some values of the variables. </br>\r\n		<br> It is better to keep values which are different prime number like 2,3,5,7,11,13,17 etc. The bigger the substitutions,higher is the accuracy but it may be time consuming. </br>\r\n		<br>Value of 1 and 0 will not work since if some element are b and b/a and we keep a=1. Then both element will act as same. In this case,Keeping values a=1, b=2 and c=5 works.   </br>\r\n		<br> Then, above question will become  $ \\begin{bmatrix}\r\n						1 & 6& 5 \\\\\r\n						1 & 3& 8 \\\\\r\n						1 & 2& 9\r\n						\\end{bmatrix}  = $ 1(27-16)-6(9-8)+5(2-3)=0</br>\r\n		 <br> And the option will become, a=0, b=1, c=6 and d=11. </br>\r\n		 <br> Since, option a matches question value. It is correct answer. Students better try same question with values a=2, b=3 and c=5.', 0),
(30, '$ \\begin{bmatrix}\r\n						a-b-c  & 2a& 2a \\\\\r\n						2b & b-c-a& 2b \\\\\r\n						2c & 2b& c-a-b\r\n						\\end{bmatrix} $ =', '(a+b+c)<sup>2</sup>', '(a+b+c)<sup>3</sup>', '(ab+bc+ca)', 'none', 'b', 'The question can be solved dimensionally. </br>\r\n		<br> The terms in the determinant are dimensionally same. Multiply diagonal element. We get term of degree 3. <br>\r\n		<br> Among options, option a is of degree 2, option b is of degree 3 and option c is also of degree 2. <br>\r\n		<br> Option b matches degree(dimension) of question. So, it is correct answer. </br>\r\n		<br> Dimension analysis can be used to eliminate wrong answer rather than finding right answer. If all other option are wrong. Then surely, the dimensionaly correct option is correct answer.', 0),
(31, '$ \\begin{bmatrix}\r\n						1  & \\log_{x} y & \\log_{x} z \\\\\r\n						\\log_{y} x & 1 & \\log_{y} z \\\\\r\n						\\log_{z} x & \\log_z y& 1\r\n						\\end{bmatrix} $ =', 'log(xyz)', '1', '0', 'none', 'c', 'Important Concept for logarithm function is $ \\log_{a} b = \\dfrac{logb}{loga} $ </br>\r\n		<br> Hence, suppose value which are power or some values like 2,4,8 or 3,9,27. So, </br>\r\n		<br> $ \\log_{x} y = \\log_{2} 4 = \\log_{2} 2^2=2 $ </br>\r\n		<br> $ \\log_{x} z = \\log_{2} 8 = \\log_{2} 2^3 =3 $ </br>\r\n		<br> $ \\log_{y} x = \\dfrac{logx}{logy} = \\dfrac{log2}{log4} = \\dfrac{1}{2} $\r\n		<br> $ \\log_{z} y = \\dfrac{logy}{logz} = \\dfrac{log4}{log8} = \\dfrac{2log2}{3log2}= \\dfrac{2}{3} $\r\n		<br> Hence, $ \\begin{bmatrix}\r\n						1  & 2 & 3 \\\\\r\n						1/2 & 1 & 3/2 \\\\\r\n						1/3 & 2/3& 1\r\n						\\end{bmatrix} =$ 1(1-1)-2 $ \\left ( \\dfrac{1}{2} - \\dfrac{1}{2} \\right ) + 3 \\left ( \\dfrac{1}{3} - \\dfrac{1}{3} \\right ) = 0 $. </br>\r\n		<br> Hence, correct option is C.', 0),
(32, 'If A = $ \\begin{bmatrix}\r\n						a & 0  & 0 \\\\\r\n						0 & a  & 0 \\\\\r\n						0 & 0  & a\r\n						\\end{bmatrix} ,$ then A<sup>n</sup> =', 'A<sup>n</sup>a<sup>n</sup>', 'Aa<sup>n+1</sup>', 'a<sup>n-1</sup>A', 'aA<sup>n+1</sup>', 'c', 'Substitute n=1 then A<sup>1</sup>=A </br>\r\n		<br> Option a= aA </br>\r\n		<br> Option a= Aa<sup>2</sup> </br>\r\n		<br> Option a= A </br>\r\n		<br> Option a= aA<sup>2</sup> </br>\r\n		<br> Hence, correct option is option C.', 0),
(33, '$ \\begin{bmatrix}\r\n						-a^2& ab  & ac \\\\\r\n						ab & -b^2  & bc \\\\\r\n						ac & bc  & -c^2\r\n						\\end{bmatrix} =$', '4a<sup>2</sup>b<sup>2</sup>c<sup>2</sup>', 'a<sup>2</sup>+b<sup>2</sup>+c<sup>2</sup>', '0', '$ \\dfrac{1}{abc} $', 'a', 'Multiplying diagonal elements gives term of degree 6 . </br>\r\n		<br> Only option a is of degree 6. Hence, it is the correct answer.', 0),
(34, 'If the ratio of the roots of x<sup>2</sup> + px = 0 be equal to the ratio of the roots of x<sup>2</sup>+lx+m=0 then,', 'p<sup>2</sup>m=l<sup>2</sup>q', 'q<sup>2</sup>p= l<sup>2</sup>m', 'pq=ln', 'pq+lm=0', 'a', 'Here, if the roots of first equation is 6,12 are roots of second equation (i.e. ratio is 3) </br>\r\n		<br> x<sup>2</sup>+px+q =0  $ \\Rightarrow $ x<sup>2</sup>-6x+8 =0 $ \\Rightarrow $ p=-6, q=8 </br>\r\n		<br> x<sup>2</sup>+lx+m =0 $\\Rightarrow $ x<sup>2</sup>=-18x+54=0 $\\Rightarrow $ l=-18, m=54 </br>\r\n		<br> Now, substitute these values in options. Only option a satisfies the equation. So, it is correct answer.', 0),
(35, 'If one root of the equation x<sup>2</sup>-px+q=0 be twice the other then,', '2p<sup>2</sup> =9q', '4p<sup>2</sup> = 7q', '2p = 9q<sup>2</sup>', '12q=5p<sup>2</sup>', 'a', 'Suppose, the roots are 2 and 4.Then, x<sup>2</sup>-px+q=0 $ \\Rightarrow $ x<sup>2</sup>-6x+8=0 $ \\Rightarrow $ p=6,q=8 </br>\r\n		<br> a) 2*36 = 9*8 (satisfied) </br>\r\n		<br> b) 4*36 = 7*8 (not satisfied) </br>\r\n		<br> c) 2*6 = 9*64 (not satisfied) </br>\r\n		<br> d) 12*8 = 5 * 36 (not satisfied) </br>\r\n		<br> Hence, correct option is a.', 0),
(36, 'If the equation x<sup>2  </sup>+ax+b=0 and x<sup> 2 </sup>+a<sup> 1 </sup>+b<sup> 1 </sup>=0 have a common root then the common root is,', '$ \\dfrac{b-b^1}{a-a^1} $', '$ \\dfrac{b+b^1}{a^1-a} $', '$ \\dfrac{b-b^1}{a^1-a} $', 'none', 'c', 'Suppose roots of the equation satisfying the question. Let the common root be 2. Then the roots are 2,3 and 2,4. Then, </br>\r\n		<br> x<sup>2  </sup>+ax+b=0 $ \\Rightarrow $ x<sup>2  </sup>-5x+6=0 $ \\Rightarrow $ a=-5, b=6 </br>\r\n		<br> x<sup> 2 </sup>+a<sup> 1 </sup>+b<sup> 1 </sup>=0 $ \\Rightarrow $ x<sup>2</sup>-6x+8=0 $ \\Rightarrow $ a<sup> 1 </sup>=-6, b<sup> 1 </sup> =8 </br>\r\n		<br> a) $ \\dfrac{b-b^1}{a-a^1} $ =  $ \\dfrac{6-8}{-5+6} $ = -2 </br>\r\n		<br> b) $ \\dfrac{b+b^1}{a^1-a} $ = $ \\dfrac{6+8}{-6+5} $ = -14 </br>\r\n		<br> c) $ \\dfrac{b-b^1}{a^1-a} $ = $ \\dfrac{6-8}{-6+5} $ = 2 </br>\r\n		<br> Option c has common root. hence, it is correct option.', 0),
(37, 'If the roots of the equation x<sup>2</sup>+ax+c=0 differ by 1, then', 'a<sup>2</sup>= ac+1', 'a<sup>2</sup>=4c+1', 'c<sup>2</sup>=4a', 'a<sup>2</sup>=c+2', 'b', 'The roots differ by 1. Let the roots be 2,3. </br>\r\n		<br> Then, x<sup>2</sup>-5x+6=0 $ \\Rightarrow $ a=-5, =6. </br>\r\n		<br> 25= -30+1 ( not satisfied) </br>\r\n		<br> 25=24+1  ( satisfied) </br>\r\n		<br> 36= -20  ( not satisfied) </br>\r\n		<br> 25=8  ( not satisfied) </br>\r\n		<br> Hence, option b is correct.', 0),
(38, '<br> $ \\sqrt { 1 + 2x + 3x^2 + 4x^3 + ........} , \\left \\vert x \\right \\vert < 1, $ is equal to,', '1 - x<sup>2</sup> + x<sup>4</sup>-..............', '1 + x<sup>2</sup> + x<sup>4</sup>+..............', '1 - x + x<sup>2</sup> - x<sup>3</sup> + ..............', '1 + x + x<sup>2</sup> + x<sup>3</sup> + ................', 'd', 'Here, power is increasing, so select a value of x such that the terms after 3 or 4 terms can be neglected. , so let x=0.1. Then, </br>\r\n		<br>  $ \\sqrt{1 + 2 \\times 0.1 + 3{ (0.1) }^2 + 4 { ( 0.1 ) }^3 + ........ } = \\sqrt{1.234} = 1.111 $ </br>\r\n		<br> a) 1 - 0 - 1<sup>2</sup> + 0.1<sup>4</sup> = 0.9901 </br>\r\n		<br> b) 1 + 0.1<sup>2</sup> + 0.1<sup>4</sup> = 1.0101 </br>\r\n		<br> c) 1 - 0.1 + 0.1<sup>2</sup> - 0.1<sup>3</sup> = 0.909 </br>\r\n		<br> d) 1 + 0.1 + 0.1<sup>2</sup> - 0.1<sup>3</sup> = 1.111 </br>\r\n		<br> Hence, correct option is d.', 0),
(39, 'If (1+x)<sup>n</sup> = C<sub>0</sub>+ C<sub>1</sub>x+C<sub>2</sub>x<sup>2</sup>+........... + C<sub>n</sub>x<sup>n</sup>, </br>\r\n		<br> then $ C_0^2+C_1^2+C_2^2+......... + C_n^2 = $', '$ \\dfrac { 2^n -1}{ (n+1)! }  $', '$ \\dfrac { (2n)! }{n!} $', '$ \\dfrac { (2n)! }{(n!)^2} $', '(2n)!', 'c', 'Put n=3, then question becomes </br>\r\n		<br> (3C0)<sup>2</sup>+(3C1)<sup>2</sup>+(3C2)<sup>2</sup>+(3C3)<sup>2</sup>= 20 </br>\r\n		<br> Put n=3 in options. Then, </br>\r\n		<br> a) $ \\dfrac{2^3-1}{ (3+1)!} = \\dfrac{7}{24} $ </br>\r\n		<br> b) $ \\dfrac{ ( 2 \\times 3)! } {3!} $ =120 </br>\r\n		<br> c) $ \\dfrac{ ( 2 \\times 3 )! } {3! \\times 3!} $ =20 </br>\r\n		<br> d) $ (2 \\times 3)! $ =720 </br>\r\n		<br> Hence, correct option is c.', 0),
(40, 'If (1+x)<sup>n</sup> = C<sub>0</sub>+ C<sub>1</sub>x+C<sub>2</sub>x<sup>2</sup>+........... + C<sub>n</sub>x<sup>n</sup>, </br>\r\n		<br> C<sub>0</sub>+2C<sub>1</sub>+3C<sub>2</sub>+................+(n+1)C<sub>n</sub>=', '2 + 2n', '2<sup>n</sup> + (n-1)2<sup>n-1</sup>', '2<sup>n+1</sup>(n+2)', '2<sup>n</sup>+n.2<sup>n-1</sup>', 'd', 'Here, put n=3. Then, </br>\r\n		<br> (3C0)+2*(3C1)+3*(3C2)+4*(3C3) = 20 </br>\r\n		<br> a)2+2*3 =8 </br>\r\n		<br> b)2<sup>3</sup> + (3-1)2<sup>3-1</sup>=16</br>\r\n		<br> c)2<sup>4</sup> * (5) = 80 </br>\r\n		<br> d)2<sup>3</sup>+3 * 2<sup>3-1</sup> = 8 + 12 = 120 </br>\r\n		<br> Hence, correct option is d.', 0),
(41, 'The series 1+ $ \\dfrac{3}{2!} + \\dfrac{7}{3!}+  \\dfrac{15}{4!} + ..... \\infty $ is equal to', 'e(e+1)', 'e(1-e)', 'e(e-1)', '3e', 'c', 'Add upto the fraction, after which all others term become negligible. </br>\r\n		<br> Here, 1 + 1.5 + 1.1667 + 0.625 + 0.2583 + 0.0875 = 4.6375 </br>\r\n		<br> use e= 2.7182 from calculator ans check the options. </br>\r\n		<br> a)10.11 b)-4.671 c)4.671 d)8.155 </br>\r\n		<br> The correct option is c.', 0),
(42, '$ \\dfrac{ 1 + \\dfrac{1}{2!} + \\dfrac{1}{4!} + \\dfrac{1}{6!}......... \\infty }{1 + \\dfrac{1}{3!} + \\dfrac{1}{5!} = \\dfrac{1}{7!}..... \\infty } $=', '$ \\dfrac{e^2-1}{e^2+1} $', '$ \\dfrac{e+1}{e-1} $', '$ \\dfrac{e-1}{e+1} $', '$ \\dfrac{e^2+1}{e^2-1} $', 'd', 'Addition of $ \\dfrac{1}{6!} or \\dfrac {1}{7!} $ to 1 does not change te total value significantly. So, we can neglect this term, </br>\r\n		<br> Then, $ \\dfrac{1 + \\dfrac{1}{2!} + \\dfrac{1}{4!} } {1 + \\dfrac{1}{3!} + \\dfrac{1}{5!} } $ = 1.3121 </br>\r\n		<br> You can neglect option a and c because by observation $ \\dfrac{1}{2!} $ is greater than $ \\dfrac{1}{3!} $ and $ \\dfrac{1}{4!} $ is greater than $ \\dfrac{1}{5!} $. </br>\r\n		<br> So, check value of b and d only. </br>\r\n		<br> b)$ \\dfrac{2.72+1}{2.72-1}= $ 2.163 </br>\r\n		<br> d) $ \\dfrac{2.72^2+1}{2.72^2-1}= $ 1.3125 </br>\r\n		<br> Hence, correct option is d.', 0),
(43, '1 + $ \\dfrac{1+a}{2!} + \\dfrac{1+a+a^2}{3!}+ \\dfrac{1+a+a^2+a^3}{4!}............. \\infty = $', '$ \\dfrac{e^a-e}{a-1} $', '$ \\dfrac{e+1}{a-1} $', '$ \\dfrac{e}{a-1} $', '(a+1)2e', 'a', 'Select value of a such that after 3 or 4 terms fraction part becomes negligibe. </br>\r\n		<br> Put a= 0.1 then, </br>\r\n		<br> 1 + $ \\dfrac{1+a}{2!} + \\dfrac{1+a+a^2}{3!}+ \\dfrac{1+a+a^2+a^3}{4!} $ </br>\r\n		<br> = 1+0.55+ 0.185 + 0.0463 </br>\r\n		<br> =1.7813 </br>\r\n		<br> a) $ \\dfrac{e^0.1 - e}{0.1-1} = $ 1.7923 </br>\r\n		<br> b) $ \\dfrac{e+1}{0.1-1} = -4.1314 </br>\r\n		<br> c) $ \\dfrac{e}{0.1-1}= -3.0203 </br>\r\n		<br> d) (0.1+1)2*e = 5.98 </br>\r\n		<br> Hence, correct optin is a.', 0),
(44, 'The value of i<sup>2069</sup>', 'i', 'i<sup>2</sup>', 'i<sup>3</sup>', 'i<sup>4</sup>', 'b', 'Rules: i<sup>1</sup>=i , i<sup>2</sup>=-1(even power of 2), i<sup>3</sup>=-i</br>(odd power of 3) and i<sup>4</sup>=1(even power of 4) </br>\r\n		<br> Hence, When you divide the power by 4, </br>\r\n		<br> if it is .25 then i, </br>\r\n		<br> if it is .5 then i<sup>2</sup>, </br>\r\n		<br> if it is .75 then i<sup>3</sup>, </br>\r\n		<br> if it is 0 then i<sup>4</sup>=1 </br>\r\n		<br> Divide 2069 by 4=517.25, hence, answer is option i.', 0),
(45, 'The value of w<sup>14342</sup>=?', 'w', 'w<sup>2</sup>', 'w<sup>3</sup>=1', '0', 'a', 'Here, w<sup>3</sup>=1, so divide the power by 3. After division, </br>\r\n		<br> if it is .33 then w </br>\r\n		<br> if it is .66 then w<sup>2</sup> </br>\r\n		<br> if it is .0 then w<sup>3</sup> </br>\r\n		<br> $ \\dfrac{14342}{3} = 4780.667 $ </br>\r\n		<br> After decimal there is .667. So, answer is b.', 0),
(46, 'The value of $ (1+i)^4 { \\left ( 1 + \\dfrac{1}{i} \\right ) }^4 $ is,', '12', '8', '16', '32', 'c', 'Take the modulus value i.e. </br>\r\n		<br> $ \\qquad \\left \\vert (1+i)^4 { \\left ( 1 + \\dfrac{1}{i} \\right ) }^4 \\right \\vert $ </br>\r\n		<br> $ =  \\left [ { ( \\sqrt{2} ) }^4 \\times { \\left ( \\sqrt { (1)^2 + { \\left ( \\dfrac{1}{i} \\right ) }^2 }^4 \\right ) } \\right ] $ </br>\r\n		<br> =4*4=16 </br>\r\n		<br> Hence, correct option is c.', 0),
(47, 'The square root of (8+6i) are:', '$ \\pm $(2+3i)', '$ \\pm $(3-4i)', '$ \\pm $(3+i)', '$ \\pm ( \\sqrt{2} + 3i ) $', 'c', 'Take the modulus of the given expression. $ \\sqrt{8^2+6^2} $ =10. </br>\r\n		<br> Now assume the question as to be the sqaure roots of 10 is? </br>\r\n		<br> a) $ \\left \\vert 2+3i \\right \\vert $ </br>\r\n		<br> b) $ \\left \\vert 3-4i \\right \\vert $ </br>\r\n		<br> c) $ \\left \\vert 3-i \\right \\vert $ </br>\r\n		<br> d) $ \\left \\vert \\sqrt{2} +3i \\right \\vert $ </br>\r\n		<br> Hence, required answer is c.', 0),
(48, 'The square roots of (8-15i) are :', '$ \\pm \\dfrac{1}{ \\sqrt{2} }(5+3i) $', '$ \\pm ( 3 + \\sqrt{2} i ) $', '$ \\pm $ (3+5i)', '$ \\pm \\dfrac{1}{ \\sqrt{2} }(5-3i) $', 'd', 'Take the modulus sign of $ \\left \\vert 8 -15i \\right \\vert = \\sqrt{8^2+15^2} $ =17 </br>\r\n		<br> Hence, the question can be assumed as root of  17 are </br>\r\n		<br> Take modulus of options a= $ \\pm \\sqrt{17} $, b= $ \\pm \\sqrt{11} $, c= $ \\pm \\sqrt{34} $ and d= $ \\pm \\sqrt{17} $ </br>\r\n		<br> Now, option a or d right? confused? </br>\r\n		<br> Consider square root of a+ib as x+iy </br>\r\n		<br> Then, i) If b is (+)ve, we should take same sign of x and y. </br>\r\n		<br>      ii) If b is (-)ve, we should take opposite sign of x and y. </br>\r\n		<br> In our question, b is -ve. So, x and y should be of opposite sign which is in option d. </br>\r\n		<br> Therefore, correct answer is option d.', 0);
